cli_content:
IP-EIGRP Topology Table for AS(100)/ID(192.168.1.1)

Codes: P - Passive, A - Active, U - Update, Q - Query, R - Reply, r - Reply status

P 10.1.1.0/24, 1 successors, FD is 2816
        via 192.168.2.1 (2816/2816), Ethernet0
P 10.1.2.0/24, 1 successors, FD is 2688
        via 192.168.3.1 (2688/2688), Ethernet1
P 10.1.3.0/24, 2 successors, FD is 2176
        via 192.168.4.1 (2176/2176), Ethernet2
        via 192.168.5.1 (2176/2816), Ethernet3
textfsm_template:
Value CODES (\S+)
Value NETWORK (\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+\/\d+)
Value SUCCESSORS (\d+)
Value FD (\d+)
Value INTERFACE (\S+)
Value VIA (\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+)
Value METRIC_RX (\d+)
Value METRIC_TX (\d+)

Start
  ^${CODES}\s+${NETWORK},\s+${SUCCESSORS}\s+successors,\s+FD\s+is\s+${FD}\s+$$
  ^\s*via\s+${VIA}\s+\(${METRIC_RX}/${METRIC_TX}\),\s+${INTERFACE}\s*$$ -> Record
